It has been observed an increasing discrepancy between the supply and demand of cadaveric organs for transplantation for a few years, particularly in renal transplantation. For this living organ donation will occupy an lasting place also in Germany. The new regulation organ donatio and transplantation in Germany provides a legal protection and prohibits all forms of organ trading. First of all the transplant team have to take into consideration medical and psychological aspects of donor and recipient but a detailed enlightenment of the pair concerning risks, complications and long term outcome is important as well.  
